        "_account_id": 302,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "paf@cray.com",
        "username": "paf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2018-03-06 20:02:13.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nThis is a quick, nasty hack that needs cleanup and improvement in various ways, but should be more or less correct.  It's a proof of concept to show what I'm suggesting for tiny writes and append.\n\nIt sort of works, though I did just manage to panic it unexpectedly.  I stress this is *very* sloppy and not intended for landing.  If people think the basic approach (described in LU-10782) is worthwhile, I will try to find time to do this right.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "64297d1bfa2bf4d08cf66bcea8b8590f52961e7a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 549,
        "name": "Misc Code Checks Robot (Gatekeeper helper)",
        "username": "smatchreview",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2018-03-06 20:03:28.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(1 comment)\n\n1 code warning(s).\nIf you believe the warnings are incorrect, please leave a comment with your explanations as a reply to the warning.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "3eaae4f679bdcf9e45259373db7bf7b47837cf72",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 302,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "paf@cray.com",
        "username": "paf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2018-03-06 20:05:05.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nBenchmark:\n8 byte append w/dd:\ndd if=/dev/zero bs=8 oflag=append of=./testfile\n3.6 MB/s w/patch\n~720 KB/s w/out patch\n\nSo about a 4x improvement, in a pretty narrow case.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "19e44363b9504c892604a358b30b914895d4ee12",
